But , oh , my dear , my dear ! such glum discussions are so sadly out of place on such a night as this , he lamented . 
For it is a night of pearl like radiancies and velvet shadows and delicate odors and big friendly stars that promise not to gossip , whatever happens . 
It is a night that hungers , and all its undistinguishable little sounds are voicing the night's hunger for masks and mandolins , for rope ladders and balconies and serenades . 
a night wherein I gratefully remember so many beautiful sad things that never happened . 
